"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish James Patrick, Kieran, Pegeen, Brendan, Caitlin, Dymphna, Dympna, Lorcan, Roisin, Siobhan.","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Deoradháin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Deoradhán</i>’, a byname representing a diminutive of <i>deoradh</i> ‘pilgrim, stranger, exile’."],"variants":[{"name":"Dorian","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Cecile, Celestine, Etienne, Jacques.  Armenian Ara, Anahid, Ashot, Garo, Houry, Saro.","Irish (Donegal and Down): variant of   Doran  .","Romanian: from a short form of the personal name <i>Teodorian</i>, derived from <i>Teodor</i>, Greek <i>Theodōros</i> (see   Theodore  )."]},{"name":"Dorrian","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Seamus.","Irish: County Down and Donegal variant of   Doran  ."]},{"name":"Dorrance","meanings":["Scottish (Ayrshire and Kircudbrightshire): variant of Irish   Doran  , with excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Doran was born on 4 August 1070, in Dundee, Scotland, United Kingdom. He married Mary Jane Handy. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died about 1110, in his hometown, at the age of 41."},"et":{"4 August 1070–about 1110":"4. august 1070–umbes 1110","1073–1095":"1073–1095","1095–1153":"1095–1153","1070–1110":"1070–1110","about 1095":"umbes 1095","4 August 1070":"4. august 1070","Aft 1095":"pärast 1095","1110":"1110","1153":"1153","about 1110":"umbes 1110","1095":"1095","1073":"1073","1070":"1070","Montrose, Angus, Scotland":"Montrose, Forfarshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Dundee, Angus, Scotland":"Dundee, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"4 August 1070–about 1110":"4. elokuuta 1070–noin 1110","1073–1095":"1073–1095","1095–1153":"1095–1153","1070–1110":"1070–1110","about 1095":"noin 1095","4 August 1070":"4. elokuuta 1070","Aft 1095":"1095 jälkeen","1110":"1110","1153":"1153","about 1110":"noin 1110","1095":"1095","1073":"1073","1070":"1070","Montrose, Angus, Scotland":"Montrose, Forfarshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dundee, Angus, Scotland":"Dundee, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"4 August 1070–about 1110":"4 août 1070–environ 1110","1073–1095":"1073–1095","1095–1153":"1095–1153","1070–1110":"1070–1110","about 1095":"environ 1095","4 August 1070":"4 août 1070","Aft 1095":"après 1095","1110":"1110","1153":"1153","about 1110":"environ 1110","1095":"1095","1073":"1073","1070":"1070","Montrose, Angus, Scotland":"Montrose, Forfarshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Dundee, Angus, Scotland":"Dundee, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Doran est né le 4 août 1070, à Dundee, Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Il a épousé Mary Jane Handy. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé environ 1110, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 41 ans."},"de":{"4 August 1070–about 1110":"4. August 1070–um 1110","1073–1095":"1073–1095","1095–1153":"1095–1153","1070–1110":"1070–1110","about 1095":"um 1095","4 August 1070":"4. August 1070","Aft 1095":"nach 1095","1110":"1110","1153":"1153","about 1110":"um 1110","1095":"1095","1073":"1073","1070":"1070","Montrose, Angus, Scotland":"Montrose, Forfarshire, Schottland, United Kingdom","Dundee, Angu